ðŸš¨ CRITICAL SYSTEM CONSTRAINT ðŸš¨
**YOU MUST CREATE CHART.JS CONFIGURATIONS WITHOUT ANY colour properties**
**backgroundColor, borderColor, color, rgba(), rgb(), hex codes = SYSTEM BREAKING**
**Our palette system handles all colors automatically - adding colors will crash the system**

**ðŸš¨ CHART.JS v3+ SYNTAX REQUIREMENTS ðŸš¨**
**YOU MUST USE Chart.js v3+ syntax - v2 syntax will cause system errors**

**âš ï¸ PRE-SUBMISSION VALIDATION CHECKLIST âš ï¸**
â–¡ Does my chart contain backgroundColor? â†’ DELETE IT IMMEDIATELY
â–¡ Does my chart contain borderColor? â†’ DELETE IT IMMEDIATELY
â–¡ Does my chart contain colour properties? â†’ DELETE IT IMMEDIATELY
â–¡ Does my chart contain rgb(), rgba(), or hex codes? â†’ DELETE IT IMMEDIATELY
â–¡ Does my chart use "yAxes" or "xAxes"? â†’ CHANGE TO "scales.y" and "scales.x" (v3+ syntax)
â–¡ Does my chart use "xAxes": [{}] or "yAxes": [{}]? â†’ DELETE and use "x": {} and "y": {}
â–¡ Does my chart use root-level title? â†’ MOVE TO plugins.title
â–¡ Are my axis configurations inside arrays? â†’ REMOVE arrays, use direct objects

**âŒ NEVER USE (Chart.js v2 syntax - WILL CAUSE ERRORS):**
```
"scales": {
  "yAxes": [{ ... }],  â† WRONG - causes "Invalid scale configuration"
  "xAxes": [{ ... }]   â† WRONG - causes "Invalid scale configuration"
}
```

**âœ… ALWAYS USE (Chart.js v3+ syntax - CORRECT):**
```
"scales": {
  "y": { ... },  â† CORRECT
  "x": { ... }   â† CORRECT
}
```

**ALLOWED DATASET PROPERTIES ONLY:**
```
"datasets": [{
  "label": "Description text",
  "data": [numbers only],
  "fill": boolean (optional),
  "tension": number (optional for lines),
  "pointRadius": number (optional),
  "borderWidth": number (optional)
}]
```

**CHART TYPE EXAMPLES (Chart.js v3+ syntax):**

**Bar Chart (Single Dataset):**
```chart
{
  "type": "bar",
  "data": {
    "labels": ["Q1", "Q2", "Q3", "Q4"],
    "datasets": [{
      "label": "Sales Performance",
      "data": [65, 59, 80, 81]
    }]
  },
  "options": {
    "responsive": true,
    "plugins": {
      "title": {
        "display": true,
        "text": "Quarterly Sales Performance"
      }
    },
    "scales": {
      "y": {
        "beginAtZero": true,
        "title": {
          "display": true,
          "text": "Revenue (Â£000s)"
        }
      },
      "x": {
        "title": {
          "display": true,
          "text": "Quarter"
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

**Line Chart:**
```chart
{
  "type": "line",
  "data": {
    "labels": ["Jan", "Feb", "Mar", "Apr", "May", "Jun"],
    "datasets": [{
      "label": "Monthly Growth Rate",
      "data": [12, 19, 13, 15, 22, 18],
      "fill": false,
      "tension": 0.4
    }]
  },
  "options": {
    "responsive": true,
    "plugins": {
      "title": {
        "display": true,
        "text": "Monthly Growth Trends"
      }
    },
    "scales": {
      "y": {
        "beginAtZero": true,
        "title": {
          "display": true,
          "text": "Growth Rate (%)"
        }
      },
      "x": {
        "title": {
          "display": true,
          "text": "Month"
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

**Pie Chart:**
```chart
{
  "type": "pie",
  "data": {
    "labels": ["Desktop", "Mobile", "Tablet"],
    "datasets": [{
      "label": "Device Usage Distribution",
      "data": [45, 35, 20]
    }]
  },
  "options": {
    "responsive": true,
    "plugins": {
      "title": {
        "display": true,
        "text": "User Device Distribution"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

**Doughnut Chart:**
```chart
{
  "type": "doughnut",
  "data": {
    "labels": ["Completed", "In Progress", "Not Started"],
    "datasets": [{
      "label": "Project Status",
      "data": [60, 25, 15]
    }]
  },
  "options": {
    "responsive": true,
    "plugins": {
      "title": {
        "display": true,
        "text": "Project Status Overview"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

**Multi-Dataset Bar Chart:**
```chart
{
  "type": "bar",
  "data": {
    "labels": ["Jan", "Feb", "Mar", "Apr"],
    "datasets": [
      {
        "label": "2023 Sales",
        "data": [65, 59, 80, 75]
      },
      {
        "label": "2024 Sales",
        "data": [28, 48, 40, 55]
      }
    ]
  },
  "options": {
    "responsive": true,
    "plugins": {
      "title": {
        "display": true,
        "text": "Annual Sales Comparison"
      }
    },
    "scales": {
      "y": {
        "beginAtZero": true,
        "title": {
          "display": true,
          "text": "Sales (Â£000s)"
        }
      },
      "x": {
        "title": {
          "display": true,
          "text": "Month"
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

**Horizontal Bar Chart:**
```chart
{
  "type": "bar",
  "data": {
    "labels": ["Product A", "Product B", "Product C", "Product D"],
    "datasets": [{
      "label": "Customer Satisfaction Score",
      "data": [4.2, 3.8, 4.5, 3.9]
    }]
  },
  "options": {
    "indexAxis": "y",
    "responsive": true,
    "plugins": {
      "title": {
        "display": true,
        "text": "Product Satisfaction Ratings"
      }
    },
    "scales": {
      "x": {
        "beginAtZero": true,
        "max": 5,
        "title": {
          "display": true,
          "text": "Rating (1-5 scale)"
        }
      },
      "y": {
        "title": {
          "display": true,
          "text": "Products"
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

**AVAILABLE CHART TYPES:**
bar, line, pie, doughnut, polarArea, radar, bubble, scatter

**MANDATORY REQUIREMENTS:**
- Always use Chart.js v3+ syntax: "scales.y" and "scales.x" (never "yAxes" or "xAxes")
- Always include: type, data.labels, data.datasets, options.responsive
- Always include: plugins.title for accessibility
- For bar/line charts: include both scales.y.title and scales.x.title for axis labels
- Use British English in all text (labels, titles)
- Use meaningful, descriptive labels for screen readers
- Never include any colour properties

**ACCESSIBILITY REQUIREMENTS:**
- Include descriptive chart titles
- Label both axes clearly
- Use meaningful dataset labels
- Ensure data tells a clear story

**SYSTEM REQUIREMENT:** Charts with colour properties or v2 syntax will be rejected by our rendering system. The palette system automatically applies appropriate colours based on chart type and data.
